               <person instant="false"><!--donor-->
                  <persName corresp="PRS0000" instant="false" full="yes">The name of the original donor Tälawe Krǝstos (fol. 226vb), has been erased throughout the Ms (sometimes the first letter of his name remained, e.g. fol. 69vb l.14).&#xD;
According to Additio 12, the Ms. was bought by priests ʾabunä Wäldä Mikaʾel and his son ʾabunä Täklä Haymanot and donated to the church of Yoḥannǝs Mäṭmǝq Dǝbla. The names of the donors, and other names (of their relatives?), are written in the supplication formulas in a recent hand: Wäldä Mikaʾel (e.g., fols. 4ra, 5rc, 5vc), Täklä Haymanot (fols. 3ra, 5va, 6rc), (ʾAmätä) Ṣädalä Maryam (fols. 6ra, 32ra, 57va), Wälättä Kidan (fols. 31va, 68vc, 172vc), Wäldä Yoḥannǝs (fols. 82ra, 87ra, 88rc), Gäbrä ʾArägawi (fols. 82ra, 91ra, 129vc), Gäbrä Yoḥannǝs (fols. 84rb), Mäzgäbä Śǝllase (fols. 151ra, 152rc, 156ra), Wäldä Giyorgis (fols. 172vb, 182rc, 191vb), Gäbrä ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer (fols. 198vc, 208ra, 209rc).&#xD;
&#xD;
The same names are indicated in Ms. DMD-009; some of the names are found in Ms. DMD-012.</persName>
